    "title": {
        "rendered": "MatR: Joe Grushecky and Bruce Springsteen: I Was Born to Rock"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "<p>If every rocker needs a mission statement, for Joe Grushecky, &#8220;I Was Born to Rock&#8221; is a pretty great candidate.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/GNbJlqlWVCI?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Tucked deep into Joe&#8217;s otherwise weighty <em>Somewhere East of Eden</em> album (his seventeenth studio album, released in 2013), &#8220;I Was Born to Rock&#8221; is crunchy and catchy, playfully and powerfully personal.</p>\n<p>And unlike many of Joe&#8217;s songs we&#8217;ve listened to here on the Shuffle, this one is 100% Grushecky&#8211;no Springsteen co-writer credit here.</p>\n<p>But with a title like &#8220;I Was Born to Rock&#8221; and team-ups so frequent they already number more than fifty, it was probably inevitable that Bruce would join Joe on stage for it if not in the studio.</p>\n<p>That moment came in May 2014, when Bruce joined Joe for a pair of Pittsburgh shows immediately following the High Hopes Tour. &#8220;I Was Born to Rock&#8221; came out for the encores, and while Bruce only supports on guitar and backing vocals, it was a roaring performance and an encore highlight.</p>\n<p>Take a listen below and enjoy Joe and Bruce&#8217;s only team-up to date on &#8220;I Was Born to Rock.&#8221;</p>\n<div id=\"v-TTD71Lro-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='426' src='https://videopress.com/embed/TTD71Lro?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen></iframe><script src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<p><strong>I Was Born to Rock<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> May 22, 2014 (Pittsburgh, PA)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> May 22, 2014 (Pittsburgh, PA)</p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
    "excerpt": {
        "rendered": "<p>One time only: Bruce joins Joe Grushecky on stage for a ferocious performance of Joe\u2019s \u201cI Was Born to Rock.\u201d</p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
